at least 10 people have died of drowning and snake-bites in northern Bangladesh .
last month, landslides triggered by heavy rains killed at least 126 people in southeastern city of Chittagong on the bay of Bengal .
the country is criss-crossed by a network of 230 rivers and suffers annual floods .
a shortage of boats hampered efforts to reach 500,000 people trapped with no access to food or clean water .
